reviews.review_text: great show this is just overall great show and great sound quality.
NRPS also available Do yourself a favor and d/l the NRPS opening set from the same night.  Excellent show, excellent sound quality.

mix.. i am not hearing a great quality recording here------the mix is bad--jerry sounds like he is hiding around the bend playing-------very low in the mix----sounds like some mics were bled into the board-----peaking levels also present----

i KNOW a better recording exists.... it was offered via BT on bt.etree.org a while ago.  due to a computer problem, i wasnt able to grab it.  if i can get it though, i will upload it (or if anyone else feels so inclined...).  taft auditorium is a beautiful theater in downtown cincinnati, and i would have loved to see the dead here.  now if we can only get a copy to sound as good as the NRPS set from this night.....

3 stars, but only because of the recording quality...a better one does exist
